service-description: The Data Vocabularies Tool is a service for describing libraries and application profiles as linked data models. This tool allows the logical data modeling process of public administration data to be open and public, which eases the utilization of data models across organizational boundaries.
show-as-file-description: Choose the file format to display the data model in. The file opens in a new tab.
site-description-1: The interoperability platform maintained by the Digital and Population Data Services Agency provides tools for defining interoperable data content. The platform consists of the terminologies, codesets and data models needed for data flows and in other areas of information management.
site-description-2: The interoperability platform is intended for both public administration and the private sector. The platform tools are available free of charge for terminology work, the management of code sets and data modelling. Data content producers are responsible for their own data specifications and their quality, and for keeping them up to date.
site-description-3: You can also use the data specifications that exist on the interoperability platform. Using existing codesets and data models in your own system development is cost-effective and improves interoperability between the systems of different actors. The consistent use of concepts makes services easier to plan and understand.
site-login-info-1: Log in with your eDuuni ID. Logging in is needed for editing the content in this web site.
site-login-info-2: You can create new eDuuni ID in eDuuni service.

tooltip.allowed-values: List of values that are allowed for the property. E.g. blue, white, green.
tooltip.association-targets-class: The class that acts as the target of an association which creates a semantical relation between two classes.
tooltip.associations-functional: Boolean, indicating that this association is functional. It means that the property can only have one value for a given individual.
tooltip.associations-identifier: Identifier (character string) that identifies the association in this data model. The identifier must be unique, so that no other resource (association, attribute or class) has that same identifier.
tooltip.associations-source: The class that acts as the source of an association which creates a semantical relation between two classes. Starting point of the relation.
tooltip.associations-target: The class that acts as the target of an association which creates a semantical relation between two classes. Ending point of the relation.
tooltip.attributes-functional: Boolean, indicating that this attribute is functional. It means that the property can only have one value for a given individual. E.g. mathematical constant ""pi"" must equal 3.14.
tooltip.attributes-identifier: Identifier (character string) that identifies the attribute in this data model. The identifier must be unique, so that no other resource (association, attribute or class) has that same identifier.
tooltip.class: Any resource that has a given property is an instance of one or more classes. E.g. the parent class asserts that this domain is restricted only to individuals that are adult persons with one or more children.
tooltip.class-identifier: Identifier (character string) that identifies the class in this data model. The identifier must be unique, so that no other resource (association, attribute or class) has that same identifier.
tooltip.data-type: Property range (or datatype) that is chosen from the list of interoperable datatypes (mainly XSD datatypes).
tooltip.default-value: Default value of the property that may be used if no other value is manually given. E.g., white if no other colour has been entered.
tooltip.disjoint-classes: Disjoint classes cannot have any individuals in common. E.g. both organization and person are inferred to be subclasses of party, but an individual cannot be both an organisation and a person at the same time.
tooltip.equivalent-associations: A semantically similar property (in another data model). For example, employedBy might be called isEmployedBy in another ontology.
tooltip.equivalent-attributes: A semantically similar property (in another data model). For example, employedBy might be called isEmployedBy in another ontology.
tooltip.equivalent-classes: Semantically equivalent class that is defined in external data model. E.g. human being - person.
tooltip.in-use-in-this-model: Boolean that indicates if the resource is in use (activated) in the data model or not (in latter case, deactivated). If yes, the resource is shown in the visualisation and can be used in schema generation or validation.
tooltip.larger-or-as-large-as: The value of the attribute must be greater than or equal to the value given here.
tooltip.larger-than: The value of the attribute must be greater than the value given here.
tooltip.maximum-amount: Cardinality restriction, indicating the maximum count of the properties. E.g. 1 when only one property is allowed, * when the number of properties is unlimited.
tooltip.maximum-length: Maximum length of the property value.
tooltip.minimum-amount: Cardinality restriction, indicating the minimum count of the properties. E.g. 0 indicates that property is optional, 1 indicates that there must be at least one property.
tooltip.minimum-length: Minimum length of the property value.
tooltip.reflexive: A property reflexivity states that the property is connected to itself. E.g. an organisation may be a part of another organisation, i.e., a subsidiary is an organisation itself.
tooltip.required-value: Fixed value for the property. E.g. a bicycle has exactly two wheels.
tooltip.smaller-or-as-small-as: The value of the attribute must be less than or equal to the value given here.
tooltip.smaller-than: The value of the attribute must be less than the value given here.
tooltip.string-attribute-format: Regular expression that can be used to validate the property values. E.g. if the attribute is ""email"", this value is required to contain character ""@"".
tooltip.string-attribute-languages: Allowed language tags for each attribute value are limited by a given list of language tags.
tooltip.target-association: Reference to the association in the core data model (core vocabulary) that forms the basis of the association restriction in this data model.
tooltip.target-attribute: Reference to the attribute in the core data model (core vocabulary) that forms the basis of the attribute restriction in this data model.
tooltip.target-class-profile: Reference to the class in the core data model (core vocabulary) that forms the basis of the shape (class restriction) in this data model (application profile).
tooltip.technical-description: Textual description of the resource, providing further information on the resource and its usage.
tooltip.transitive: Association that can be inferred from another association. E.g. if there is a relation that A is the employer of B, then B is an employee of A.
tooltip.upper-associations: A semantically more general association. E.g. relative is an upper association to parent.
tooltip.upper-attributes: A semantically more general attribute. E.g. address is an upper attribute to postal address.
tooltip.upper-classes: An semantically more general class, upper class in class hierarchy. E.g. person is an upper class to a patient class.
tooltip.utilizes-class-restriction: Select a shape (class restriction) in another data model (namespace) to be applied also to this datamodel.

you-can-try-to-reload-the-page-or-the-re: You can try to reload the page or the resource does not exist.
